atleast that's how monks do it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 862<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/3/02 4:15:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on weapon use</span><hr size=1> Well, since you're a warrior...<br>
<br>
First off, damage bonus is applied to each hit with the mainhand weapon. This is why the Lammy (9/19) outdamages a Gorganga Club (14/27 I think?)  even though the gorganga has a better ratio.  Also, you do more taunt if you hit faster.  So basically, you want fast weapons, and you want the fastest main hand.  Also, you want procs, as they give taunt... debuff procs are best.  You'll do more damage offhand with the Centi LS than a Lammy, but a bit more taunt most likely, though it's close.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
Dawn Rising <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 529<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/3/02 6:36:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on weapon use</span><hr size=1> As Jarkell said, for a warrior, you don't want a Centi in your primary hand because of the slower delay, but they make great offhand weapons.<br>
<br>
In primary hand, a lamentation will outdamage the centi (faster delay = more primary hand dmg bonus), but in secondary hand the centi will outdamage the lamentation (better ratio &amp; str bonus).<br>
<br>
Since you're actually looking for an offhand upgrade, pretty sure the Centi's a better choice for ya.<br>
<br>
- Syll / Kat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhoraciofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HoracioFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/3/02 8:03:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lol</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> but they make great offhand weapons<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
   For a ranger mabey.. not for a class thats primary purpose is to hold agro. And there is no way in hell a 14-27 weapon is even going to oudamage a 9-19 weapon at lvl 53 off hand or not damage bonus or otherwise.. its just basicly to damn slow to be any good to anyone but a ranger. And that is ONLY If said ranger dosn't have Jolt or know how to use it. Then it becomes pretty much a useless weapon to anybody (unless you just cant find somthing better). At lvl 51+ any class that is still using a centi LS in my opinion is just hurting themselfs in a major way.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/4/02 12:10:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on weapon use</span><hr size=1> A 14-27 will out damage a 9-19 in offhand.<br>
<br>
And agro is about a lot of things, mostly level.  Your offhand isn't going to make a huge difference either way.<br>
<br>
-=Viren=- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 865<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/4/02 1:42:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on weapon use</span><hr size=1> For sheer damage ouput, in the offhand ratio is all that matters, thus a 9 19 will not beat a 14 27.  But the more hits you do, the more taunt, and thus a lammy will out taunt a Centi offhand... but not by that much.  Certainly not worth buying it.  <br>
<br>
But get something with some procs!<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel<br>
Dawn Rising <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhoraciofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HoracioFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/4/02 9:05:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> naw</span><hr size=1> Your off hand still uses Delay on how often you dual weild. We are talking an 8 differance in delay wich is a pretty big margin as far as delays go. You are going to swing that lamentation probably close to if not more than 25% more times than you are going to swing the PoS... er centi LS while doing aproximatly 3/4 the damage. Over the course of the fight this works out to ALOT more damage than the centi. Mabey if the off hand didnt use delay at all and just randomly &quot;proced&quot; your argument would be correct. If we are just talking damage per swing at the same rate then yeah hit for hit the centi is going to hit harder. But thats not how it works's in game.<br>
<br>
More swings=more hits=more double attacks=more damage<br>
<br>
Period <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/4/02 10:18:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on weapon use</span><hr size=1> Yes, more swings = more hits = more chances to double attack ... but this last part is wrong.<br>
<br>
The only time a Lammy in offhand will outdamage a Centi LS is when the fight is so short you can swing the lammy twice and Centi LS once =)<br>
<br>
Here... for shits and giggles...<br>
<br>
In a fight you will get to swing the lammy 42% more than a Centi LS.<br>
<br>
A Centi LS will do 55% more damage per swing than a Lammy.<br>
<br>
Now, both are influenced by double attack equally.  Lets say I'm in a fight and do 1000 damage with my offhand.  Now lets say my ability to swing my offhand goes up 10%.  I will do it 10% more often.  Do you think delay is going to matter?  It is straight percentage.  You will do ~1100 damage, 100 more, regardless of delay.  And that is exactly what offhand is, it is a percentage chance to go off based on level and skill.<br>
<br>
I'm not advocating using a Centi LS over a Lammy, but I find it rather ridiculous that you call a Centi LS a PoS, hunk of junk, and that you praise a lamentation, when in all regards, they are about the same weapon.<br>
<br>
-=Viren=- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhoraciofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HoracioFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/4/02 6:53:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lol</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> A Centi LS will do 55% more damage per swing than a Lammy.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Not a chance<br>
<br>
In a perfect world where a Cent LS hits for Maximum damage every single time. That statment would still be far from correct. <br>
<br>
<br>
10% of 27 would be 2.7 the lammy would have to be a 24.3 delay weapon for your percent to be correct but its not. Now 2.7 times 3 would be 8.1 delay points wich would be roughly 30% of 27 as a delay. 27 minus 8.1 is 18.9 wich is rougly the delay of a lamentation. So if you wan't to get right down to it the lamentation would roughly attempt to dual wield 30% more than a Centi LS. And we could generaly say that it would suceed 30% more of the time. This percentage could go up and down due to alot of factors but would generally stay fairly consistent.<br>
<br>
Now we all could argue about wich weapon will do more damage all day. The fact is there is so many factors that go into it there really is no saying. Armor class of the mob your fighting, lvl of the warrior, strength of the warrior. Weapon skill deul weild skill, lvl of the mob your fighting. All of these can be deciding factors in how much damage you do with either. But we are giving a warrior advice on what weapon would be hands down the best. And hands down the lamentation will generate more agro and come close or outdamage the Cent LS. If you don't think low delay weapons are the way the light and the power for high end warriors. Go to any high end warrior profile in say Fire and Fury or Resolution. And tell me how many of them use a weapon with a delay over 24. They just don't use them for agro reasons, not to mention when a fight takes you over 5 min to take the mob down. That 30% is going to work out to 100's of extra attacks. Wich in turn generates a cosiderable amount of extra agro. And depeding obviously on opinion you could translate those 100's of extra attacks into extra damage.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 542<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/4/02 7:07:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lol</span><hr size=1> I'll definately give you that a lamentation would generate more aggro than a centi longsword, and as holding aggro is a good thing for a warrior, that's a plus in lamentation's basket.<br>
<br>
Still not quite following you on the damage thing though.  I would think the Centi Longsword would outdamage a lamentation when used in offhand.<br>
